President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. of the United States and Prime Minister Mario Draghi of Italy met at the White House. They discussed the strong partnership between the two countries, including their alliance through NATO and the U.S. partnership with the EU. They talked about the ongoing conflict in Ukraine and expressed their commitment to supporting Ukraine and imposing costs on Russia. They also discussed measures to address the economic challenges caused by Russia's actions, particularly in the areas of food security and energy markets. The leaders pledged to continue working together on global issues such as COVID-19 and climate change, as well as on shared foreign policy challenges involving China and Libya. They anticipated further discussions at the G-7 Summit and NATO Summit in June.